a:2:{s:7:"content";s:2340:"<p>Gentis Solutions is seeking a highly motivated and detail-oriented Technical Staff Accountant to join our client's team. The successful candidate will work with global team members at varying levels of management across Finance, Reporting, Treasury, Tax, and division Controlling.&nbsp;If you are interested in joining our team, apply below.</p>
<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>
<ul><li>1+ years of relevant accounting experience in public accounting and/or large sized corporations with a focus on technical accounting, revenue recognition, lease accounting and research</li><li>Path to MBA/MAcc or CPA preferred</li><li>Strong understanding of accounting theory, controls, and US GAAP</li><li>Strong attention to detail, exceptional organizational skills, and ability to prioritize demands and meet deadlines</li><li>Advanced Excel skills</li><li>Ability to adapt to fast-paced, growth environment</li><li>Excellent written/verbal communication, interpersonal, and relationship building skills</li><li>Ability to communicate to all levels within the organization with confidence</li><li>Eager to learn and enthusiastic for gaining new, technical accounting skills</li></ul>
<p><strong>Typical Duties</strong></p>
<ul><li>Partner with foreign entities for US GAAP compliance, including the review of local statutory to US GAAP financials and support of annual foreign audits</li><li>Guide data collection needs between external audit team and the organization</li><li>Supply internal support to meet all requirements of the annual US GAAP audit</li><li>Partner with Finance Leadership for preparation of the global consolidated financial statements and disclosures</li><li>Oversee ASC 842 lease accounting, including ongoing monitoring of lease portfolio, updating lease accounting software, and being the point of contact across all entities for lease accounting questions</li><li>Oversee ASC 606 revenue recognition, including reviewing contracts, determining any adjustments needed, and being the point of contact across all entities for revenue recognition questions</li><li>Contribute to special projects and analyses on an ad-hoc basis including developing and monitoring accounting policies</li><li>Participate in group discussions, such as trainings, with regular interactions of ongoing assistance to all entities</li></ul>";s:12:"content_meta";N;}